# Build context = repo root for the 4-layer source-compiled stack at
# docker/{postgres,postgis,pgext,final}.Dockerfile + docker/entrypoint.sh +
# docker/initdb.d/. The pgext layer needs CMakeLists.txt + ext/laplace_pg/
# (including generated/*.c and generated/*.h). The postgres + postgis layers
# need external/{postgres,postgis,proj,geos} submodules.

# === .NET managed-tier (not part of native PG extension build) ===
src/**/bin/
src/**/obj/
tests/**/bin/
tests/**/obj/
bin/
obj/
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/

# === CMake / Visual Studio intermediate (multi-GB FetchContent caches) ===
ext/laplace_pg/build/
**/build/
*.user
*.suo

# === SeedTableGenerator output: TSVs (~5 GB) ===
# Bulk-loaded into PG via COPY at bootstrap, NOT compiled into the .so.
# The generated *.c and *.h files (codepoint_table.c, registries) ARE in
# context — they compile into the laplace_generated static library that's
# linked into both laplace_pg.so and laplace_native.so.
ext/laplace_pg/generated/*.tsv

# === VCS / editor / OS noise ===
.git/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# === Plans / docs / memory (not used by Docker build) ===
docs/
plans/
memory/
logs/
reports/

# === Native build artifacts that may exist alongside source (defensive) ===
*.dll
*.pdb
*.exp
*.lib

# === Old standalone Dockerfile location (superseded by docker/*.Dockerfile) ===
# infra/laplace-pg/Dockerfile is the prior school-project pattern; keep its
# directory ignored from the new layered context.
infra/laplace-pg/Dockerfile
